---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { DEFAULT_LOCALE, siteCopy } from "../content/site";

const copy = siteCopy[DEFAULT_LOCALE];
const meta = {
  title: "OpenClaw Memory Plugin | mem9",
  description:
    "Persistent cloud memory for OpenClaw with long-term recall across sessions and machines, shared memory for multi-agent workflows, hybrid search, and a visual dashboard.",
};
---

<Layout meta={meta} locale={DEFAULT_LOCALE}>
  <Navbar
    nav={copy.nav}
    aria={copy.aria}
    localeNames={copy.localeNames}
    themeOptions={copy.themeOptions}
  />

  <main class="landing">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero-shell">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">OpenClaw Memory Plugin</p>
          <h1>Persistent cloud memory for OpenClaw</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">
            mem9 gives OpenClaw long-term memory across sessions and machines, shared memory
            across agents, hybrid recall, and a visual dashboard for review, import, and export.
          </p>
          <p class="question-strip">
            How do I give OpenClaw long-term memory? How do I keep agent memory across sessions?
            How do I share memory across agents and reduce repeated context? mem9 is the plugin
            for that job.
          </p>

          <div class="cta-row">
            <a class="button primary" href="/SKILL.md" target="_blank">Open SKILL.md</a>
          </div>

          <div class="link-row">
            <a href="https://mem9.ai/your-memory">Dashboard</a>
            <a href="/#security">Security</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/mem9-ai/mem9" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="surface-card install-card">
          <p class="card-kicker">Install entry</p>
          <h2>Use ClawHub, then say one sentence</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Install mem9 from ClawHub.</li>
            <li>Start a new OpenClaw chat.</li>
            <li>Say <code>setup mem9</code> or <code>reconnect mem9</code>.</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="card-note">
            mem9 handles onboarding, reconnect, uninstall, and explicit “remember this” requests
            after setup.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="section-kicker">Why mem9</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Three reasons teams pick it over local memory files</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid three-up">
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>Persistent memory across sessions and machines</h3>
            <p>
              Restart the gateway, switch devices, or reopen a project later. Your agent memory
              stays available instead of living in fragile local files.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>Shared memory for multi-agent workflows</h3>
            <p>
              Keep one memory layer across OpenClaw sessions and agents so teammates and automation
              do not have to relearn the same context.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>Hybrid recall with a visual dashboard</h3>
            <p>
              Combine durable cloud memory with a dashboard for analysis, cleanup, import, export,
              and trust-building around what the agent remembers.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section comparison">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="section-kicker">Best for</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">When mem9 is a better fit than default memory</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid two-up">
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>Default or local memory</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Tied to one machine or one workspace</li>
              <li>Easy to lose during resets, reinstalls, and migrations</li>
              <li>Hard to review or manage across sessions</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel accent-panel">
            <h3>mem9 for OpenClaw</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Cloud-persistent memory that follows your agent</li>
              <li>Shared memory across sessions, machines, and multi-agent workflows</li>
              <li>Hybrid recall plus a dashboard for visual inspection and management</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="section-kicker">Use cases</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Problem-driven questions mem9 is built to answer</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid two-up">
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>How do I give OpenClaw long-term memory?</h3>
            <p>
              Install mem9 and let it persist important facts, preferences, and project context in
              the cloud instead of rebuilding context from scratch every session.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>How do I keep agent memory across sessions?</h3>
            <p>
              mem9 keeps memory durable across restarts, new chats, and new machines, so users do
              not have to repeat the same instructions over and over.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>How do I share memory across agents?</h3>
            <p>
              Point multiple OpenClaw agents or workflows at the same mem9 space to reuse learned
              knowledge instead of isolating it in separate local stores.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="surface-card panel">
            <h3>How do I reduce repeated context in OpenClaw?</h3>
            <p>
              mem9 stores durable facts and recalls only what matters for the current task, helping
              reduce repeated prompts, token waste, and drift across long-running work.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section final-cta">
      <div class="container surface-card cta-panel">
        <p class="section-kicker">Get started</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Install mem9, then manage memory visually</h2>
        <p class="cta-copy">
          Start from ClawHub or the public SKILL.md, then use the same mem9 credential in the
          dashboard to review, analyze, import, and export memory.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="button primary" href="/SKILL.md">Stable install guide</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="https://mem9.ai/your-memory">Open dashboard</a>
          <a
            class="button ghost"
            href="https://github.com/mem9-ai/mem9"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
          >
            Star on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer footer={copy.footer} />
</Layout>

<style>
  .landing {
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .hero-shell {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.7fr) minmax(300px, 0.95fr);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .hero-copy {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .eyebrow,
  .section-kicker,
  .card-kicker {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1,
  .section-title,
  .install-card h2 {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1.02;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.7rem, 6vw, 4.8rem);
    max-width: 12ch;
  }

  .subtitle,
  .question-strip,
  .cta-copy,
  .panel p,
  .install-card p,
  .install-card li {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 1.04rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .question-strip {
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .section {
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
  }

  .section-heading {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .three-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .two-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .panel,
  .install-card,
  .cta-panel {
    padding: 1.4rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .panel h3,
  .install-card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .panel ul,
  .install-card ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .accent-panel {
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 70%, transparent), var(--surface)),
      radial-gradient(circle at top right, color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 12%, transparent), transparent 55%);
  }

  .cta-row,
  .link-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .link-row a {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
  }

  .link-row a:hover {
    color: var(--text);
    border-bottom-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 45%, transparent);
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-height: 2.85rem;
    padding: 0 1.15rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 700;
    transition: transform 160ms ease, border-color 160ms ease, background 160ms ease;
  }

  .button:hover {
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .button.primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--bg-terminal);
  }

  .button.secondary,
  .button.ghost {
    color: var(--text);
    border-color: var(--border);
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .cta-panel {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .card-note {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
  }

  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.92em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .hero-shell,
    .three-up,
    .two-up {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hero {
      padding-top: 4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
